Count of the longitudinal scale rows of the presently reported specimen (ca. 55) was much fewer than those given by the original description of 

C. shigensis

(ca. 101; 
Kuroda 1956
). However, re-examination of the holotype of the species revealed that its count was actually ca. 60 on the left side of the body (poor condition) and 58 on the right side (Table 
1
).
